freetext.SYMPTOMS_DESCRIPTION: Bad back (painful). Pinched nerve in upper shoulder (very painful). Nothing relating to COVID-19.

I received a Shingles shot on Friday about noon. Right now is about 54 hours later and I am still experiencing moderate soreness at and around the injection site. I am quite sure that this represents a moderate reaction to the Shingles shot.
